# /Users/b/DATA/PROJECTS/Telco/.gitignore
# ============================================================
# .gitignore for Telco (tiered Levels) — allow code, ignore runs
# ============================================================
#
# QUICK GUIDE (symbol usage)
# ============================================================
# Default: ignore everything, then allowlist what we want with *
# ============================================================
# - A line without a prefix matches paths to IGNORE.
# - "!" at the start NEGATES a prior ignore (re-allow).
# - Trailing "/" means "directory".
# - "*" matches within a single path segment; "**" matches across folders.
# - Rules are evaluated top → bottom; the LAST matching rule wins.
#
# NOTES / POLICY (what should / should not be in git)
# ✅ Keep in git:
#   - source code: .py, notebooks (.ipynb), scripts
#   - configs/templates: *.yaml, *.yml, *.toml, example envs (*.env.example)
#   - docs/specs: markdown, diagrams (small), READMEs
#   - small static assets required to run examples (e.g., a tiny png)
#
# ❌ Do NOT keep in git (generated / local / heavy / sensitive):
#   - run outputs: resources/reports, resources/artifacts, figures, models, outputs
#   - datasets: any data/ folder, raw/processed files
#   - caches: __pycache__, ipynb checkpoints, logs
#   - envs: venv/.venv, site-packages
#   - secrets: tokens/keys/.env files with credentials
#
# 💡 If you want to keep folder structure without files:
#   - add an empty ".gitkeep" inside the folder you want tracked
#   - then explicitly allow it with a negation rule (see below)

# ============================================================
# Python
# ============================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# ============================================================
# Virtual environments
# ============================================================
.venv/
venv/
ENV/
env/

# ============================================================
# Jupyter Notebook
# ============================================================
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb_checkpoints

# ============================================================
# Data files (DO NOT commit datasets)
# ============================================================
data/*.csv
data/*.xlsx
data/*.parquet
data/*.pkl
data/*.json
data/raw/*
data/processed/*
!data/.gitkeep

# ============================================================
# Model files and artifacts
# ============================================================
models/*.pkl
models/*.joblib
models/*.h5
models/*.pt
models/*.pth
!models/.gitkeep

# ============================================================
# Results and outputs
# ============================================================
results/*
!results/.gitkeep
outputs/
logs/
*.log

# ============================================================
# IDE
# ============================================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# ============================================================
# Environment variables
# ============================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ============================================================
# OS
# ============================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ============================================================
# Project-specific
# ============================================================
*.backup
*.bak

# ============================================================
# Personal-notes
# ============================================================
# notes/
models/*.pkl
sample_predictions.csv
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
